text:
5th Street, Avenue B, to Avenue A.
November 24, 1918.

East 5th Street, (rear view) south side, east of Ave. A., and showing a general view northward. Buildings shown across the horizon, are the Consolidated Gas Co., the Metropolitan Life Insurance and the N.Y. Life insurance Co.

August 31, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

Avenue A. North from East 5th Street. At the right is a modern apartment house occupying the 5th to 6th street frontage. In the block above, is the Loew Hollywood Theater

May 17 1937

Works Progress Administration
Five Boroughs Project
